algorithm_technique: Iterate through character codes for columns and digits for rows to generate cell strings.
problem_summary_simple: List all Excel cells within a given range, sorted by column then row.
problem_summary_technical: Generate cell strings by iterating through column character codes and row numbers within the specified range.
key_insights: The problem leverages the ASCII values of characters to represent columns.
A nested loop structure is natural for iterating through a 2D range.
The constraints on the input string simplify parsing and range determination.
